{
  "stem": "19895.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because sometime somebody who is a university-educated type of professor, to come down to a gymnasium level, they expected from us probably an awful lot.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And probably due to many circumstances, we have been often talked-- at least, the way I felt it-- little bit above our head at times.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So many of us excelled.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And many of us just chugged along.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And like in any school, there were excellent ones and, and, and mediocre ones.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And some who failed and dropped out of school and had to go to a lower level school.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So these are the memories of the teachers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A wonderful saying, which I am borrowing from somebody who lives in Washington here, is that there must have been in your life one teacher who you remember especially.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And interesting that his memory and my memory is concentrating also around our educators in gymnastics, a teacher whose name is Zoltan Duckstein.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remember him very fondly.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Duckstein, that's D-U-- and the U has two apostrophes on it-- C-K-S-T-E-I-N.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was, himself, an excellent sportsman in, in gymnastics.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the school gymnasium, maybe for American and, and, and English education here in the, the United States, might be confusing.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The gymnasium, the school, was a scholastic athletics, as well as we have indeed excellent gymnastic education in the physical aspects and, and, and understanding of the word.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this teacher was somebody who left some very fine memories with me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So did my teacher of physics, whose name is Beno-- B-E-N-O with an apostrophe-- and last name is Strasser-- S-T-R-A-S-S-E-R.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Also, a teacher whose name is Jeno, first name, Grunwald-- I don't have to spell that.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
